      "term": "PME (Protective Multiple Earthing)",
      "simpleDefinition": "The most common UK version of a TN-C-S system where the supplier earths the combined neutral/earth conductor at multiple points along the network.",
      "anchor": "The industry name for standard TN-C-S supplies.",
      "misconception": "Thinking PME is a different system type than TN-C-S; they are effectively the same in a domestic context."
